    </teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Exodus 39</title>
                        <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Ex039-P153v-L4_trl" n="4"
                            prev="ADub.III.73.002.038.trl.xml#Ex038-P153v-L4_trl" />
                        <l n="1">And from the blue and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             purple and scarlet silk they made colourful garments,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             for doing service in the Holy, and made the holy garments
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             that were for Aaron, as the Lord commanded Moses.</l>
                        <l n="2">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             And he made the ephod of gold, blue and purple and scarlet
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             silk, and twined linen.</l>
                        <l n="3">And they did flatten
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             the gold metal sheets, and cut out wires, to work
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             it in the blue, and in the purple, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             in the scarlet silk, and in the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             linen — embroiderer’s work.</l>
                        <l n="4">They made shoulders
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             for it, joined: by the two edges it was joined together.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                        <l n="5">And the embroidery of his band that was on it was of one piece with
                            it,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             according to its work: of gold, blue <supplied reason="lost">and purple
                                and scarlet silk</supplied>, and twined
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             linen, as the Lord commanded Moses.</l>
                        <l n="6">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             they worked onyx stones enclosed in settings of gold,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             engraved with signet engravings, above the names
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             of the children of Israel.</l>
                        <l n="7">And he set them on the shoulders
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             of the ephod: stones of remembrance for the children
                            <milestone unit="page" n="154r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             of Israel, as the Lord commanded Moses.</l>
                        <l n="8">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             he made the breastplate, embroiderer’s work, like the work
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             of the ephod: of gold, blue and purple and scarlet silk, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             twined linen.</l>
                        <l n="9">It was foursquare. They made the breastplate doubled,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             a span was the length of it, and a span the breadth of it,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             being doubled.</l>
                        <l n="10">And they filled there four rows
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             of stones. A row of a ruby, an emerald, and a carbuncle:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             the one row.</l>
                        <l n="11">And the second row:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             a kohl stone, a sapphire stone, and a diamond.</l>
                        <l n="12">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             the third row: a jacinth, an agate, and an amethyst.</l>
                        <l n="13">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             And the fourth row: a beryl, an onyx, and a jasper,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             enclosed in settings of gold filigree settings.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                        <l n="14">And the stones were above the names
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             of the children of Israel, twelve, with their names,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             signet engravings, everyone with its name, according to the twelve
                            tribes.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                        <l n="15">And they made chains finished in pure gold,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             rope work, on the breastplate.</l>
                        <l n="16">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             they made two settings of gold, and two gold rings,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             and put the two rings on the two ends
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             of the breastplate.</l>
                        <l n="17"><emph>And they put the two</emph>
                            <emph>ropes of gold on the two rings on the ends of the
                                breastplate</emph>.<anchor type="addSpan" xml:id="Ex-039-add001_trl"
                             /></l>
                        <l n="18">And they put the two ends
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             of the two ropes on the two settings,
                            <milestone unit="page" n="154v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             and put them on the shoulders of the ephod,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             in the front.</l>
                        <l n="19">And they made two rings of gold,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             and put them on the two ends of the breastplate, in its edge,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             which was on the inside edge of the ephod.</l>
                        <l n="20">And they made
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             two golden rings and put them on the two shoulders
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             of the ephod underneath, in the front of it,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             toward the front of the place of being coupled, above the embroidered
                            |band| of the ephod.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                        <l n="21">And they set the breastplate by its rings
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             to the rings of the ephod with a blue string, that it may be
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             above the embroidered |band| of the ephod, and that the breastplate
                            might not be lifted
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             from the ephod, as the Lord commanded Moses.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                        <l n="22">And he made the robe of the ephod of weaver’s work,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             all of blue.</l>
                        <l n="23">And the opening of the robe in the middle of it
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             was like the opening of a coat of mail, there was an edging around the
                            opening
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             so it would not be torn.</l>
                        <l n="24">And they made on the hems
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             of the robe pomegranates of blue and purple and scarlet
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             silk, twined.</l>
                        <l n="25">And they made bells of pure
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             gold, and put the bells among
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             the pomegranates on the hems of the robe, all around
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             among the pomegranates:</l>
                        <l n="26">A golden bell and a pomegranate,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             a golden bell and a pomegranate, around the hems of the robe
                            <milestone unit="page" n="155r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             to serve in, as the Lord commanded Moses.</l>
                        <l n="27">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             And they made shirts of linen, weaver’s work, for Aaron
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             and for his sons.</l>
                        <l n="28">And a turban
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             of linen, and high caps of linen, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             dual trousers of twined linen,</l>
                        <l n="29">And a girdle of
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             twined linen and blue and purple and scarlet silk,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             of embroiderer’s work, as the Lord commanded Moses.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                        <l n="30">And they made the diadem of the holy crown of pure
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             gold, and wrote on it a writing, signet engraving,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             “<emph>Holy to the Lord</emph>.”</l>
                        <l n="31">And they put a blue string on it
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             to put it on the turban above,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             as the Lord commanded Moses.</l>
                        <l n="32">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             all the service of the tabernacle of the tent of meeting was finished,
                            and the children
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             of Israel did according to all that the Lord commanded Moses. They did
                            so.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                        <l n="33">And they brought the tabernacle to Moses,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             the tent and all its equipment, its hooks, its boards,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             its bars, and its pillars, and its bases,</l>
                        <l n="34">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             The covering of rams’ skins
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             dyed red, and the covering of porpoise skins, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             the veil of the covering,</l>
                        <l n="35">The ark of the law,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             and its poles, and the cover,</l>
                        <l n="36">
                            <milestone unit="page" n="155v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             The table, and all its vessels, and the showbread,</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                        <l n="37">The pure lampstand,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             its places for candles, candles for the row, and all its vessels,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             and the oil for light,</l>
                        <l n="38">And the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             golden altar, and the anointing oil, and the fragrant
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             incense, and the cover for the tent door,</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                        <l n="39">The bronze altar, and its grate of bronze,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             its poles, and all its vessels,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             the basin and its place,</l>
                        <l n="40">The
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             curtains of the court, its pillars, and its bases,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             and the cover for the court gate, its cords, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             its pegs, and all the vessels of the service of the tabernacle
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             for the tent of meeting,</l>
                        <l n="41">The colourful garments
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             to do service in the Holy, and the holy garments for Aaron,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             the priest, and the garments of his sons, to serve as priests.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                        <l n="42">All that the Lord commanded Moses:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             so the children of Israel did all the work.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                        <l n="43">And Moses saw all the work, and, lo,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             they had done it as the Lord had commanded. They did so. And Moses
                            blessed
                            <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Ex039-P155v-L20_trl" n="20"
                                next="ADub.III.73.002.040.trl.xml#Ex040-P155v-L20_trl" />
                             them. </l>
                    </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
